text: Alwin Out (born 27 December 1996) is a Dutch korfball player. He is a member of Koog Zaandijk and the Netherlands national korfball team. Out was top- scorer with Koog Zaandijk in 2019. With the national team he won the gold medal at the 2022 World Games in Birmingham, Alabama. ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch korfball players
